Fuse Energy
There may not be a company worth rooting harder for than Fuse Energy [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/fe1163c9-3b5c-4493-b533-71c4ef054882?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
If Fuse is successful, it will help avoid nuclear war on the way to deliver=
ing clean, abundant fusion energy. It might be our answer to The Great Filt=
er [ https://substack.com/redirect/07385720-8328-4897-a668-a69d63f4915b?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
The Great Filter, proposed by Robin Hanson in a 1996 paper by the same name=
 [ https://substack.com/redirect/5783536e-f0f1-4571-8f9b-57eb01437f31?j=3De=
yJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], suggests a=
 potential resolution of the Fermi Paradox [ https://substack.com/redirect/=
cfb49d83-47e7-48f4-b135-f08ed713a545?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]: if the probability that intelligent life ex=
ists somewhere else in the universe, why haven=E2=80=99t we met any aliens?=
=C2=A0
Hanson=E2=80=99s idea is that there must be a stage in the evolution and ex=
pansion of life that is extremely difficult to surpass. Candidates include =
the emergence of life from matter, the transition from simple prokaryotic c=
ells to complex eukaryotic cells, multicellularity, evolution of intelligen=
t life, the ability to achieve technological advancement, surviving the tec=
hnology we create (WE ARE HERE), and interstellar travel.=C2=A0
The good news is that humanity has made it past a number of potential filte=
rs. We=E2=80=99re alive and intelligent and developing ever-more powerful t=
echnologies!=C2=A0
The bad news is that, if it wasn=E2=80=99t impossible to make it this far, =
then maybe the reason we haven=E2=80=99t met any aliens is that they all de=
stroy themselves once they get to this point. =F0=9F=98=AF
There are a number of ways we could destroy ourselves before expanding thro=
ughout the universe, but two of the most commonly cited are nuclear war and=
 climate change.=C2=A0
Nuclear war and climate change are existential risks to humanity.=C2=A0
Fuse is working to mitigate both, through nuclear weapons effects testing a=
nd fusion power.=C2=A0
And if it succeeds, it might ultimately help break that final barrier - int=
erstellar travel =E2=80=93 and fulfill the dream that got JC Btaiche [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/0744e155-bdd7-431c-b787-8f613634c598?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] interested in fusi=
on in the first place.=C2=A0
Man, I really don=E2=80=99t want to leave you hanging there, but before I t=
ell you about JC=E2=80=99s dream, I need to impress upon you how different =
Fuse is from any other fusion company.=C2=A0
For one thing, JC isn=E2=80=99t a PhD. He didn=E2=80=99t even go to college=
=2E He=E2=80=99s a 24-year-old Lebanese-Ca=
nadian immigrant to America who sta=
rted Fuse in Montreal when he was 19.=C2=A0
He=E2=80=99s attracted a team that includes:=C2=A0
