The Z Machine Reborn
One of the underappreciated benefits of not having a degree, particularly a=
n advanced degree, is that you're not tied to any particular line of resear=
ch. In academia, you don=E2=80=99t choose your research based on which desi=
gn is potentially most commercially viable. The fusion research that=E2=80=
=99s most interesting to study in the lab may not make for the best busines=
s.
By not going to college, let alone getting his PhD, JC had a clean slate wh=
en deciding which generator design to pursue at Fuse.=C2=A0
To make that decision, he spoke to a number of academic researchers, each o=
f whom believed that the approach they had pursued in the lab was the right=
 approach and that it was time to spin out.=C2=A0
There are currently dozens of brilliant teams building fusion startups [ ht=
tps://substack.com/redirect/1e19505f-7955-415c-98b7-bde089d251ae?j=3DeyJ1Ij=
oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] pursuing every c=
onceivable generator design, many of which they=E2=80=99d studied for years=
 before going commercial, but none of them seemed to be asking the question=
 that JC thought was most important:=C2=A0
=E2=80=9CWhere is the government spending billions of dollars already?=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0
That question led him to the Z Machine at Sandia National Labs.
The Z Machine is the most successful nuclear program that no one has heard =
of. When Rahul Rana and I wrote The Fusion Race [ https://substack.com/redi=
rect/49a711a6-c725-4089-b226-c6d72f037182?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA=
_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], we didn=E2=80=99t mention it. Its sist=
er machine, the National Ignition Facility at Lawrence Livermore National L=
ab (NIF), gets all the headlines.=C2=A0
But the Z Machine sports an impressive list of superlatives:=C2=A0
Most Powerful X-Ray Source on Earth: x-ray bursts reach peak power of 290 t=
erawatts (TW).=C2=A0
Hotter Than the Sun: generates temperatures over 2 billion degrees Kelvin (=
K), hotter than the interior of stars and hotter even than nuclear explosio=
ns.=C2=A0
Highest Energy Pulses: discharges up to 26 million amperes (MA) of electric=
al current in nanoseconds.=C2=A0
Strong Magnetic Fields: produces some of the strongest magnetic fields on e=
arth, essential for the z-pinch process used to compress fusion fuel.=C2=A0
Like NIF, Sandia=E2=80=99s Z Machine was not designed to produce fusion pow=
er. Both were built for nuclear weapon stockpile stewardship and research i=
nto fusion and high energy density physics.=C2=A0
But NIF and Z Machine share a common mantle on the path to commercial fusio=
n: they=E2=80=99re the only two machines that have achieved the triple prod=
uct of 1020 KeV s/m3, within the order of magnitude required for scientific=
 breakeven (NIF has achieved it, Z has not yet).=C2=A0
If you=E2=80=99re going to try to produce fusion power, JC thought, why not=
 pursue one of the two paths that=E2=80=99s already generated the condition=
s necessary to do so?=C2=A0
So JC decided to build a pulsed-power generator en route to a MagLIF genera=
tor, like Z Machine. But he didn=E2=80=99t just do it because Z did; it tur=
ns out, pulsed power is a fruitful commercial path to fusion, too.=C2=A0
