tivate a neutron source =E2=80=93 like polonium-beryllium =E2=80=93 to begi=
n the process. The starter neutrons hit the uranium atom, splitting it into=
 two smaller atoms and a neutron, which flies off and hits another uranium =
atom, which splits and releases a neutron which hits another uranium atom, =
and so on. This is called going critical.
In these reactions, the neutron source is just a kickstarter =E2=80=93 it d=
oes its job, and then the chain reaction takes over.=C2=A0
But what if you had a way to consistently produce high-energy neutrons?=C2=
=A0
Fuse will. Its scheme is subcritical by nature because it relies on the fus=
ion reaction to continue producing neutrons, and therefore has none of the =
criticality concerns associated with traditional nuclear fission reactors.
In a hybrid fusion-fission reactor, like Apeiron, the D-T fusion reaction i=
n the core releases high-energy neutrons and large amounts of energy. Those=
 neutrons fire off and hit a fission blanket surrounding the core, typicall=
y made of heavy atoms like uranium and, importantly, nuclear waste such as =
spent fuel from traditional reactors.=C2=A0
The blanket captures the high-energy neutrons, which can induce fission, ge=
nerating energy, and transmute long-lived radioactive isotopes into shorter=
-lived and more stable ones, reducing the long-term radiotoxicity and volum=
e of nuclear waste.=C2=A0
The process produces power and reduces nuclear waste, both of which are val=
uable.=C2=A0
The US currently has a $40 billion Nuclear Waste Fund [ https://substack.co=
m/redirect/1c1da1fa-f68b-48b8-a956-8587c06aaa76?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J=
5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], funded by a tax on electricity, =
to build a depository for nuclear waste. It=E2=80=99s a political quagmire =
=E2=80=93 look up Yucca Mountain [ https://substack.com/redirect/14063adb-6=
4ff-44f8-a30c-dd8b8d8f9fa0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=93 and as a result, nuclear waste remains an un=
resolved and overblown impediment to nuclear=E2=80=99s growth.=C2=A0
Turning that waste into power would be a win for everyone. And Sandia found=
 that the numbers pencil out =E2=80=93 20MW, or 1019 14.1 MeV neutrons, of =
fusion output produces =E2=80=9CActinide blanket output=E2=80=9D of 3,000 M=
Wth (megawatts thermal, or heat energy). At a ~30% conversion to electrical=
, 20MW of fusion output could drive a 1 gigawatt output. And because the re=
action remains subcritical =E2=80=93 it needs the fusion reaction to contin=
ue =E2=80=93 there=E2=80=99s an easier regulatory path with the onerous Nuc=
lear Regulatory Commission (NRC).=C2=A0
To be sure, Fuse=E2=80=99s goal is to produce pure fusion energy =E2=80=93 =
to put an APEIRON fusion generator in every city in the world. By the time =
it builds a hybrid fusion-fission plant and produces electrons, that=E2=80=
=99s just an engineering challenge.=C2=A0
It will need materials that can handle higher-density currents, better tran=
smission lines, and more efficient and longer-lasting capacitors.=C2=A0
If your capacitor can only survive a million shots, and you need to replace=
 it every year, your fusion plant may not be profitable despite a high Q. =
=E2=80=9CThese are numbers a lot of fusion companies don=E2=80=99t talk abo=
ut,=E2=80=9D JC told me. But if it can survive 9 or 10 million shots, the p=
lant starts to look a lot more profitable.=C2=A0
What drew JC and the team to MagLIF is that these aren=E2=80=99t science ch=
allenges, but engineering ones. They need to figure out how to get shots fi=
red efficiently, repetitively, and cheaply, and the whole business is struc=
tured to generate revenue while simultaneously iterating away the engineeri=
ng challenges.=C2=A0
The goal is to find markets that support both near-term revenue and the opp=
ortunity to improve the engineering on the path to fusion.=C2=A0
Finding Fuse=E2=80=99s Markets=C2=A0
Now that we=E2=80=99re all fusion-familiar, let=E2=80=99s get down to busin=
ess.=C2=A0
Every fusion company is in the business of producing radiation. Most fusion=
