e cases that could make money today and contribute to progress towards fusi=
on power.=C2=A0
The rabbit holes led the team into =E2=80=9Cthis really niche, obscure worl=
d where you can=E2=80=99t find the buyers on LinkedIn or at conferences=E2=
=80=9D: nuclear effects testing.=C2=A0=C2=A0
The nuclear effects testing market is really three separate markets:
Stockpile Stewardship: Ensuring the reliability of the nation=E2=80=99s nuc=
lear weapons stockpile without underground nuclear testing by running simul=
ations using data from radiation shots.=C2=A0
Survivability: Will electronics hold up to radiation, whether a nuclear exp=
losion, electromagnetic pulses (EMP), or in space? Critical components in d=
efense and aerospace need to be radiation-hardened (rad-hard), and can cost=
 500-1000x more [ https://substack.com/redirect/eaa90996-e8f0-415c-93dc-50b=
631b971cf?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ] than non-rad-hard off-the-shelf parts.=C2=A0
Treaty Monitoring: This is the lesser known segment, but the intelligence c=
ommunity needs to know whether, say, North Korea or Iran is testing nuclear=
 weapons in defiance of international treaties, which they can do by detect=
ing radioactive particles and gasses.=C2=A0
These markets are a little tricky to size accurately, because some of the s=
pend is secret, but each is on the order of billions of dollars.=C2=A0
The overall Defense Electronics Market is a $150 billion market expected to=
 grow to over $250 billion in the next decade, per Allied Market Research [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/ce25d174-f3a9-4c63-ac4a-ca19c744f609?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. Radiation ef=
fects testing is a piece of that pie =E2=80=93 as the market grows, more te=
sting will be needed to prove rad-hardness, which Fuse can meet with the TI=
TAN II and FAETON II generators it=E2=80=99s building in California.=C2=A0
Another way to look at the market is by sizing the Radiation Effects Testin=
g Facilities Market =E2=80=93 analyzing the actual revenue generated for ra=
diation shots by the national labs, universities, and private companies tha=
t sell those shots today. NIF, for example, sells roughly 250 shots per yea=
r at $1 million per shot. By looking at 37 operational facilities, Fuse siz=
ed this market at about $2.5 billion per year.=C2=A0
These facilities sell shots =E2=80=93 or more precisely, weeks=E2=80=99 of =
time on their machines =E2=80=93 for a variety of uses, including survivabi=
lity and stockpile stewardship as well as scientific research. While both n=
ational labs and private companies do work on each, a rough way to think of=
 it is that the national labs like Sandia, Los Alamos, and Lawrence Livermo=
re do more stockpile stewardship work while private companies like VERUS Re=
search [ https://substack.com/redirect/27e88658-bab5-4d54-94b3-ce44d2fec2a3=
?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Shin=
e Fusion [ https://substack.com/redirect/0dff43ca-a55e-4be6-bab5-65b4e950ea=
45?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Ho=
neywell, and L3Harris [ https://substack.com/redirect/2a757837-2283-4ea0-90=
37-e5d54137aed2?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU ] do more survivability work.=C2=A0
As Fuse develops more powerful machines, it will be able to serve more uses=
 =E2=80=93 survivability then stockpile stewardship and treaty monitoring =
=E2=80=93 and therefore larger markets. Importantly, the path to fusion is =
also the path to winning more of the nuclear effects testing market.
To start, Fuse is focusing on survivability, or rad-hard electronics, for b=
oth the DoD and commercial customers.=C2=A0
To that end, in February, Fuse announced [ https://substack.com/redirect/dd=
3522fa-c65f-44d4-9207-51c447c42707?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaM=
ZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] that it was awarded an Air Force Small Busines=
