 me that he wants Fuse to be a multi-billion dollar vertically integrated c=
ompany building a fusion power plant in every city in the world. Doing so, =
he said, would significantly increase the GDP and independence of countries=
 that are energy-constrained today.=C2=A0
In that future, he still wants to sell shots for stockpile stewardship and =
survivability. Unfortunately, deterring nuclear war doesn=E2=80=99t make th=
e threat disappear. He=E2=80=99s even thinking about making survivability t=
esting so cheap that all of our electronics can be rad-hard and cheap.=C2=
=A0
He knows that it sounds ambitious =E2=80=93 =E2=80=9CI realize that I=E2=80=
=99m talking about five multi-billion dollar companies=E2=80=9D =E2=80=93 b=
ut the trick is that they=E2=80=99re not really five separate businesses.=
=C2=A0
The thing that excites me about Fuse =E2=80=93 apart from the obvious stuff=
 about avoiding nuclear war and producing limitless clean energy so that hu=
mans can survive and explore the universe =E2=80=93 is how beautifully the =
different stages of the company line up.=20
One thing leads to another, funded, ideally, by government partners with a =
clear and present need. Each one of those five businesses can be its own in=
creasingly valuable business, and each increases the likelihood of the next=
=2E=C2=A0
Fuse just has to focus on getting really good at producing radiation to do =
all of the useful things that radiation can do, and on finding customers wh=
o value that radiation.=C2=A0
It=E2=80=99s going to be harder than it sounds, of course. Nothing is as si=
mple as it comes across in these deep dives.=C2=A0
But everything worth doing is hard, and hard is not impossible. Fuse has a =
plan, broken down into manageable chunks on the way to a really big goal, a=
nd the team to execute against it. I, for one, am pumped that they=E2=80=99=
re going for it, and I=E2=80=99m rooting hard for JC and the team to pull i=
t off.=C2=A0
Apart from the tangible goals, it=E2=80=99s impossible not to love the idea=
 a 24-year-old immigrant building a company that might carry humanity throu=
gh the Great Filter. That=E2=80=99s the American Dream, and Fuse is fightin=
g to keep it alive.=20
