17;re willing to pour more energy into a process than you get out &#8211; s=
ay, because you want to run tests to ensure that America&#8217;s nuclear st=
ockpile still works &#8211; you can use fusion to produce </span><strong>ra=
diation</strong><span> before you can achieve Q&gt;1, or Q&gt; whatever you=
&#8217;d need to profitably produce electricity. Roughly, the higher your t=
riple product, the more radiation you can produce.</span></p><h4 class=3D"h=
