r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">In a pulsed-power generator, multiple capacitors are charged in parallel =
to a high voltage. When it&#8217;s time to fire a shot, a trigger closes al=
l of the switches, reconfiguring the capacitors from a parallel arrangement=
 to a series arrangement. In a series arrangement, the voltages of the indi=
vidual capacitors add up, so if each capacitor is charged to 100 volts and =
there are 10 capacitors, the total output voltage becomes 100 x 10, or 1000=
 volts (1 kV).&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>That pulsed power can be us=
