current that creates a magnetic field around a gas, compressing it into a p=
lasma (with less current). The inward force of the magnetic field increases=
 the pressure and temperature of the plasma &#8211; this is known as the </=
span><strong>pinch effect</strong><span> &#8211; which can theoretically cr=
eate conditions suitable for nuclear fusion.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
