 text-decoration: underline;">Dr. Rick Spielman</a><span>, the former Chief=
 Scientist of the Z Machine and a leading expert in pulsed power.&#160;</sp=
an></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>TITAN will be used as a building block for f=
uture Fuse machines, and as a source of radiation for testing in its own ri=
ght. While it won&#8217;t produce neutrons &#8211; it&#8217;s 0.6 MA isn&#8=
217;t a strong enough current to implode a liner &#8211; it will produce ra=
diation. It can be connected with a </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/=
redirect/13f5a31a-0e77-4a39-b32a-62fd7dda43f3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
 text-decoration: underline;">Bremsstrahlung source</a><span> to produce ho=
t x-rays for hostile nuclear effects testing or with an </span><a href=3D"h=
ttps://substack.com/redirect/0a711cbc-c653-4ed8-81bc-09981c1f8948?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">electron beam source</a><=
span> for electron beam testing.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">After pr=
oving out the TITAN I and FAETON I prototypes in Montreal, Fuse is opening =
up a US headquarters in San Leandro, California, where it will build TITAN =
II and FAETON II with a fully US-compliant supply chain in order to sell sh=
ots to the government.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Even with the US-co=
mpliant supply chain, these generators will cost Fuse in the single-digit m=
illions, a portion of which it hopes the government will cover. Each shot t=
hese machines fire is worth tens of thousands of dollars to customers at ~9=
0% margins to Fuse, it can fire as many as 50 in a day, and given undersupp=
ly, demand shouldn&#8217;t be an issue. As such, </span><strong>paybacks ma=
y be well under one year.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
Over time, the economics may get even better. If TITAN I was the prototype,=
 TITAN II will be built for scale, for a couple of reasons.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">First, which we&#8217;ll discuss a little later, because Fuse m=
ay sell TITAN IIs to other fusion companies. And second, because Fuse&#8217=
;s own future machines &#8211; Z STAR and Apeiron &#8211; will need a lot o=
f TITANs.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Z STAR</strong><span>, the mid=
-scale pulsed power facility Fuse plans to launch in 2027, would consist of=
 16 TITANs in a ring, shooting all of their power at one MagLIF target in t=
he center (likely D-T fuel). The Z STAR will have a peak power of roughly 1=
5 TW.&#160;</span></p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static" style=
