TITANs&#8217; </span><em>currents</em><span> add up in Z STAR since they&#8=
217;re connected in parallel.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Delivering =
12.8 MA of current is an important milestone, because </span><strong>it tak=
es at least 10 MA of current to implode a liner and produce neutrons</stron=
g><span>. Z STAR will produce &#8220;10</span><sup>14</sup><span> D-T,&#822=
1; or 100 trillion deuterium-tritium reactions. Since each D-T reaction pro=
duces one neutron, </span><strong>Z STAR will produce 100 trillion neutrons=
 per shot.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Z STAR is an in=
termediate step towards Fuse&#8217;s creation of a next gen Z Machine, or N=
ext Generation Pulsed Power (NGPP) Machine.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As J=
C described it to me, just as the Laboratory of Laser Energetics&#8217; OME=
GA facility at the University of Rochester (where Dr. Spielman works) serve=
s the laser community as an intermediate facility to NIF, Z STAR will serve=
 the pulsed power community as an intermediate facility to the Z Machine. A=
nd like OMEGA, Z STAR will likely be housed at a research university. Fuse =
is currently in talks with one in particular which would provide the buildi=
ng to host Z STAR, a $30 million value. Fuse currently expects to have Z ST=
AR online in 2027.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>If Z STAR is an interme=
diate step, </span><strong>APEIRON I </strong><span>is the destination. APE=
IRON I is a planned 50-70 MA machine that would serve as Fuse&#8217;s first=
 fusion pilot plant.&#160;</span></p><div class=3D"captioned-image-containe=
