yle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;"><span>To start, Fuse is focusing on </span><strong>survivabili=
ty</strong><span>, or rad-hard electronics, for both the DoD and commercial=
 customers.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To that end, in Februar=
y, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/dd3522fa-c65f-44d4-9207-=
51c447c42707?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Fus=
e announced</a><span> that it was awarded an Air Force Small Business Innov=
ation Research (SBIR) contract for the development of TITAN. It recently su=
bmitted a Phase II SBIR application for TITAN II, which would cover half th=
e CapEx cost of the machine.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The company =
is also in advanced talks with commercial customers to buy shots from its g=
enerators, an important step in the company&#8217;s plans to sell </span><s=
trong>radiation-as-a-service</strong><span>, instead of selling weekly time=
 on a generator like national labs and private competitors do.&#160;</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Commercial customers might include defense contractor=
s who need to rad-hard the electronics in the products they build, or space=
 companies whose satellites need to withstand the intense radiation outside=
 the protective blanket of the earth&#8217;s atmosphere.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Fuse believes it can win a growing share of the radiation effects=
 testing facilities market because there are several issues with the market=
 as it stands:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=
=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizi=
ng: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Undersupply and L=
ong Lead Times: </strong><span>Most existing facilities are overbooked and =
have lead times longer than one year.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"mar=
gin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: bor=
der-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>National Labs Even Slowe=
r: </strong><span>National Lab access takes two years of contracting and bu=
reaucratic overhead.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px=
; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-botto=
m: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Aging Facilities Require Maintenance</str=
ong><span>: The problem will get worse, as older facilities like Sandia&#82=
17;s SATURN and L3Harris&#8217; PITHON go offline for maintenance for over =
a year.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special=
-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding=
-left: 4px;"><strong>Weekly Booking versus Per-Shot: </strong><span>Most fa=
cilities are booked by the week, which incentivizes slower data collection.=
 Fuse plans to do 50+ shots per day versus the 5-10 per day that competitor=
s fire.&#160;</span></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Fuse&#8217;s long-term =
development is focused on the TITAN branch &#8211; from TITAN to Z STAR to =
APEIRON &#8211; because it&#8217;s better suited for both nuclear weapons s=
tockpile testing, nuclear waste mitigation through hybrid fusion-fission, a=
nd fusion power.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When it decided to go down the =
TITAN path, however, it didn&#8217;t ditch FAETON, because FAETON is partic=
ularly valuable for survivability testing (and fusion research) as it stand=
s today. It can simulate the effects of various types of radiation (gamma r=
ays, neutrons, protons) on electronic components, ensuring they can withsta=
nd and operate reliably in high-radiation environments such as space or nea=
r nuclear reactors.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">To that end, FAETON II is being bu=
ilt with pre-booked demand from survivability customers, specifically those=
 who will be impacted when L3Harris&#8217; PITHON and Sandia&#8217;s SATURN=
 go offline in the coming years.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In the near-ter=
m, Fuse actually expects to make more money from FAETON II shots than it do=
es from TITAN II shots, because the value of FAETON II&#8217;s neutron-prod=
ucing shots are twice as valuable as TITAN II&#8217;s.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">Over the next two years, the company expects to make $10 million fro=
m the two devices ($2 million of which is already contracted), and over the=
 next decade, it projects that it can generate over $300 million of revenue=
 from FAETON II alone, at gross margins of roughly 90% per shot. Even in th=
e first stage or the plan, this is a good business. </p><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">B=
ut the real bet on Fuse is that it can build a valuable, cash-flowing busin=
ess in radiation effects testing with increasingly valuable call options on=
 nuclear weapons effects testing, nuclear waste mitigation through hybrid f=
usion-fission, and ultimately, fusion power.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rg=
b(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Tho=
se call options rely on the TITAN track.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-=
