"><strong>Modernizing the Nuclear Arsenal</strong><span>&#160;</span></h3><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">On the way to fusion power, Fuse plans to help America mod=
ernize and maintain its nuclear arsenal in order to deter the threat of nuc=
lear war in the face of rising tensions with nuclear adversaries.&#160;</p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">In March, Sandia National Labs, on behalf of the NNSA, is=
sued a Request for Information (RFI) for a public-private partnership to bu=
ild the next Z Machine, a billion-dollar-scale project inspired by the NASA=
 COTS program that launched SpaceX.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In April, Fu=
se entered into a five-year Cooperative Research and Development Agreement =
(CRADA) with Sandia, which operates under the NNSA, under which they share =
research and development on Next Generation Pulsed Power.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
