; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position=
: relative;"><strong>What if it Works?</strong><span> </span></h3><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>If it succeeds, Fuse will solve one of humanity&#8217;s big=
gest challenges: delivering clean, abundant energy to power the continued e=
volution of our species without killing our home planet. It will also earn =
a seat in what </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/71a04b69-61f=
0-4c08-af78-0fb62b43fdce?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: und=
erline;">Bloomberg predicts will be a $40 trillion market</a><span>. Fusion=
 power might even let SpaceX travel beyond Mars.&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">A parallel is not a guarantee. SpaceX has already executed brilli=
antly against much of its plan. Most of Fuse&#8217;s plan is still on paper=
=2E But the company has proven a lot wi=
th a little, and the strategy is sound=
=2E It&#8217;s the most practical path=20=
to fusion, with the most valuable wayp=
oints, that I&#8217;ve seen.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When I asked JC wha=
t his vision for the company in twenty years is, he told me that he wants F=
use to be a multi-billion dollar vertically integrated company building a f=
usion power plant in every city in the world. Doing so, he said, would sign=
ificantly increase the GDP and independence of countries that are energy-co=
nstrained today.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In that future, he still wants =
to sell shots for stockpile stewardship and survivability. Unfortunately, d=
eterring nuclear war doesn&#8217;t make the threat disappear. He&#8217;s ev=
en thinking about making survivability testing so cheap that all of our ele=
ctronics can be rad-hard and cheap.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>He kno=
ws that it sounds ambitious &#8211; &#8220;I realize that I&#8217;m talking=
 about five multi-billion dollar companies&#8221; &#8211; but the trick is =
that they&#8217;re not really five </span><em>separate </em><span>businesse=
s.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The thing that excites me about Fuse &=
#8211; apart from the obvious stuff about avoiding nuclear war and producin=
g limitless clean energy so that humans can survive and explore the univers=
e &#8211; is how beautifully the different stages of the company line up. <=
/p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">One thing leads to another, funded, ideally, by govern=
ment partners with a clear and present need. Each one of those five busines=
ses can be its own increasingly valuable business, and each increases the l=
ikelihood of the next.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Fuse just has to focus on=
 getting really good at producing radiation to do all of the useful things =
that radiation can do, and on finding customers who value that radiation.&#=
160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s going to be harder than it sounds, of =
course. Nothing is as simple as it comes across in these deep dives.&#160;<=
/p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But everything worth doing is hard, and hard is not im=
possible. Fuse has a plan, broken down into manageable chunks on the way to=
 a really big goal, and the team to execute against it. I, for one, am pump=
ed that they&#8217;re going for it, and I&#8217;m rooting hard for JC and t=
he team to pull it off.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Apart from the tangible =
goals, it&#8217;s impossible not to love the idea a 24-year-old immigrant b=
uilding a company that might carry humanity through the Great Filter. That&=
#8217;s the American Dream, and Fuse is fighting to keep it alive. </p><div=
